<content>
<theme id="thm215">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Notes tied to a triplet</title>
<tocimage>img215.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson a new rhythmic pattern is introduced, by tying a note to a triplet:</para>
<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4 noVisible)(n * q l)(n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)
        (n * e g+)(n * e l g-)(n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>
<para>Note the difference between the first and the second measure, and
between the third and the fourth. Note how
they are formed when tying the note to the triplet:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4)(n * q)(n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)
        (n * q l)(n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)
        (n * e g+)(n * e g-)(n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)
        (n * e g+)(n * e l g-)(n * e g+ t3)(n * e)(n * e g- t-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>
</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm215_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear and practise the
introduced rhythmic patterns.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm215_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

